Suppose $M$ and $N$ are compact, irreducible 3-manifolds with empty or incompressible toral boundary which are not closed $Sol$-manifolds. Let $f:\widehat{\pi_1M}\to \widehat{\pi_1N}$ be an isomomrphism. Then $f$ induces a {congruent isomorphism} between graphs of profinite groups
$$
f_{\bullet}\;: (\widehat{\mathcal{G}^M},\Gamma^M)\xrightarrow{\;\;\cong\;\;} (\widehat{\mathcal{G}^N},\Gamma^N)
